Latest Posts

The Best Men Can Be

   Posted on January 22, 2019 by kierandonaghy
   8 Comments

   This ELT lesson plan is designed around a viral short film commissioned
   by the brand Gillette. In the lesson students watch a short film, speak
   about masculinity, read a transcript and Twitter comments and write
   their own Twitter comment.   … Continue reading →

Ian

   Posted January 16, 2019

   This ELT lesson plan is designed around a short film titled Ian
   inspired by the true story of a boy of the same name. The film was
   commissioned by Fundación ian, a foundation set up by the boy’s mother
   animated … Continue reading →

Can I help you with anything?

   Posted May 30, 2018

   This ELT lesson plan is designed around a short film which was created
   for Kindness.org, a charity that encourages people to take part in acts
   of kindness and share them online. In the lesson students predict the
   content of a … Continue reading →

A Single Life

   Posted January 3, 2018

   This ELT lesson plan is designed around a short film by Job, Joris &
   Marieke and the theme of stages of life. In the lesson students
   practise vocabulary related to the stages of life, discuss stages of
   life, watch a … Continue reading →

